Kenya president Uhuru Kenyatta. (File: City Press) Multimedia &nbsp; &nbsp; User Galleries &nbsp; &nbsp; News in Pictures Send us your pictures &nbsp; &nbsp; Send us your stories Nairobi - Patrick Njoroge has been formally appointed as the new governor of the Central Bank of Kenya by the president after parliament approved the choice, the central bank said on its website.President Uhuru Kenyatta also appointed Jairus Mohammed Nyaoga as the bank's board chairperson and Sheila M'Mbijjewe as the second deputy governor. "Their four-year term of office is effective from June 19 2015," the bank said. 24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.